      • testCreateWardCorrect

        public void testCreateWardCorrect()
        Tries to create a Ward object using the method BasicDBService.createWard(String, int). As the Ward object must not be directly stored after creating, this test checks if a Ward object exists in db, yet it should not.
        Involved methods:
        • BasicDBService.createWard(String, int)
        • PersistentObject.getObjectID()
        • Ward.getName()
        • Ward.getNumberOfBeds()
        • BasicDBService.getWards()

      • testStoreWardInsertGetWard

        public void testStoreWardInsertGetWard()
        Tries to insert and get a Ward object using the BasicDBService.store(PersistentObject) and BasicDBService.getWard(long) methods. Test succeeds if
        1. storing the Ward object succeeds
        2. the number of all Ward objects in db increases by one
        3. getting the Ward object via its objectID succeeds
        4. the given Ward object is part of all Ward objects via BasicDBService.getWards()
        5. the received Ward object matches the given one
        Involved methods:
        • BasicDBService.createWard(String, int)
        • BasicDBService.getWards()
        • BasicDBService.store(PersistentObject)
        • BasicDBService.getWard(long)
        • Ward.getName()
        • Ward.getNumberOfBeds()
        • PersistentObject.getObjectID()

      • testStoreWardUpdateGetWard

        public void testStoreWardUpdateGetWard()
        Tries to update and get a Ward object using the BasicDBService.store(PersistentObject) and BasicDBService.getWard(long) methods. Test succeeds if
        1. storing the Ward object succeeds
        2. the number of all Ward objects in db does not change
        3. getting the Ward object via its objectID succeeds
        4. the given Ward object is part of all Ward objects via BasicDBService.getWards()
        5. the received Ward object matches the given one
        Involved methods:
        • BasicDBService.createWard(String, int)
        • BasicDBService.getWards()
        • BasicDBService.store(PersistentObject)
        • BasicDBService.getWard(long)
        • Ward.setName(String)
        • Ward.getName()
        • Ward.setNumberOfBeds(int)
        • Ward.getNumberOfBeds()
        • PersistentObject.getObjectID()
